# üìù Lovable for Polkadot

## üåü Project Overview

Polkadot is the most resillient and flexible chain out there, so let's make it the default choice by making it easy for Web3 builders to Ship!

This project is to create a Lovable clone for web3 creators to type in an app they want to create and have AI automatically build it in the correct way for the Polkadot ecosystem.

This is a great way to go a step further than an LLM that's fine-tuned / RAGging docs, and help developers apply the tech to their idea. By making it easy, more projects will be started, and founders can spend less energy building and more energy commercialising.

We're passionate because we believe AI software builders are the future, and want to build this for the leading technology in the ecosystem. 


### üîç Project Details

Technical approach:
 - Fork Bolt.diy (an open source Lovable clone)
 - Edit the order of prompts and LLMs being called to work well for Polkadot
 - Add boilerplate projects for each of the common project types on Polkadot (super lightweight for LLM to work with)
 - Test how well it builds the common project types, and keep editing the prompts to do a great job.

To make this possible:
 - Learn how to build on the Polkadot chain
 - Learn what the common project types are
 - Build each of the common project types (e.g. games, defi, AI, tokens, marketplaces), then make a super lightweight version of each
 - Add documentation for the LLM to know how to customise them for the users' specific app idea.


### üß© Ecosystem Fit

Once stable, this project can appear in Polkadot docs and enable all Polkadot developers to get started quickly with Polkadot.


