## üìä Development Status

We have a Lovable clone that can build a Polkadot app, but it doesn't consistently work. We need to find the failure modes and adapt the LLMs to consistently work.
Then we need to do the work in the Project Details section.

## üìÖ Development Roadmap

Milestone 1: Stable build of a Polkadot Dapp
 - AI can produce a stable build on the first shot
 - Grant application team can recieve a link, enter a prompt, and see a rendered app on the first shot (works for one type of app). They can keep prompting to edit, fix, and extend.

Milestone 2: Multiple projects supported
 - Multiple common Polkadot project types supported (not just one)
 - Grant application team can prompt-generate multiple project types.

Milestone 3: Extensibility for Polkadot ecosystem documented
 - Publish article, share it with the Polkadot ecosystem, find out what they want and where the project should go from here.
 - Documented process for training the LLM to build further projects, so Polkadot team or ourselves can add project types easily
 - Unit testing, refactoring, prepare for extensibility
 - Grant application team can see Docs, Tests, Article, and Notes on what external people want to see.

### Overview

- **Estimated Duration:** Duration of the whole project (maximum 3 months)
- **Full-Time Equivalent (FTE):**  Average number of full-time employees working on the project
- **Total Costs:** Requested amount in USD for the whole project (maximum $10,000 USD)

> Note that deliverables 0a to 0d are mandatory. Please adapt their specification to your project.

| Number | Deliverable | Specification |
| -----: | ----------- | ------------- |
| 0a. | License: MIT |
| 0b. | Documentation | We will provide both **inline documentation** of the code and a basic **tutorial** that explains how a user can contribute to the open source project |
| 0c. | Testing and Testing Guide | Core functions will be fully covered by comprehensive unit tests to ensure functionality and robustness. In the guide, we will describe how to run these tests. |
| 0d. | Article | We will publish an **article** that explains what was done/achieved as part of the grant. |
| 1. | Stable builds | Users can prompt the AI to build a Polkadot Dapp |
| 2. | Mulitple projects | Multiple project types will be supported |
| 3. | Extensibility | Docuentation and refactoring to make it easy for the project to be taken beyond the current vision |

